functions.name: AreaClearAllPeds
functions.desc: Removes all pedestrian from the area.

functions.name: AreaGetVisible
functions.desc: Returns the current area code.

functions.name: CameraDefaultFOV
functions.desc: Sets camera FOV to default value. Resets changes made from ```CameraSetFOV```.

functions.name: CameraFade
functions.desc:
Fades the camera in or out, in the specified milliseconds.

Fade out: 0
Fade in: 1

functions.name: CameraGetFOV
functions.desc: Get the camera FOV.

functions.name: CameraReturnToPlayer
functions.desc: Sets the camera focus back to the player.

functions.name: CameraSetFOV
functions.desc: Set the camera FOV.

functions.name: CameraSetXYZ
functions.desc: Sets the camera position to the first three arguments, and sets the camera look position to the last three.

functions.name: ChapterGet
functions.desc: Gets the current chapter.

functions.name: ChapterSet
functions.desc: Sets the current chapter.

functions.name: ClockGet
functions.desc: Gets the current time.

functions.name: ClockIsPaused
functions.desc: Check if the game clock is paused or not.

functions.name: ClockSet
functions.desc: Manipulates the in-game time.

functions.name: ClothingBackup
functions.desc:
Stores what the player is currently wearing.

You'll probably want to use this along with ```ClothingRestore```.

functions.name: ClothingRestore
functions.desc: Sets the player the saved clothing at the time of calling ```ClothingBackup```.

functions.name: DisablePunishmentSystem
functions.desc: Disables the troublemeter.

functions.name: EffectSetGymnFireOn
functions.desc: Sets a red filter on the screen.

functions.name: GetTimer
functions.desc: Returns the time passed in milliseconds since the game started.

functions.name: PauseGameClock
functions.desc:
Stops time and turns off clock HUD.

You'll probably want to use this along with ```UnpauseGameClock```.

functions.name: PedCreateXYZ
functions.desc:
Creates a character at the specified location.

The ped will be tied to the current script so that it is cleaned up when the script terminates, and will of course be returned for you to script with.

functions.name: PedDelete
functions.desc: Delete existing pedestrian.

functions.name: PedGetFaction
functions.desc:
Get the faction id of the existing ped.

**Faction ID**

0. PREFECT
1. NERD
2. JOCK
3. DROPOUT
4. GREASER
5. PREPPY
6. STUDENT
7. COP
8. TEACHER
9. TOWNPERSON
10. SHOPKEEP
11. BULLY
12. DEFAULT
13. PLAYER1
14. PLAYER2

functions.name: PedGetHeading
functions.desc: Get the ped rotation in radian.

functions.name: PedGetHeadPos
functions.desc: Get the ped's head coordinate.

functions.name: PedGetHealth
functions.desc:
Sets a ped's health.

Will raise max health if set higher than their current max health.

functions.name: PedGetLastVehicle
functions.desc: Get the last driven vehicle.

functions.name: PedGetMaxHealth
functions.desc: Get the maximum ped health.

functions.name: PedGetMoney
functions.desc: Get the amount of money the ped has.

functions.name: PedGetNodeTime
functions.desc: Get the animation time in millisecond.

functions.name: PedGetOffsetInWorldCoords
functions.desc: Get the position based on ped's position as the center.

functions.name: PedGetPosXYZ
functions.desc: Returns the ped's coordinates.

functions.name: PedGetTargetPed
functions.desc:
Get the ped's current target.

Returns ```nil``` if the ped isn't targetting any other ped.

functions.name: PedGetTypeToTypeAttitude
functions.desc:
Get the ```A``` attitude towards ```B```.

**Faction ID**

0. PREFECT
1. NERD
2. JOCK
3. DROPOUT
4. GREASER
5. PREPPY
6. STUDENT
7. COP
8. TEACHER
9. TOWNPERSON
10. SHOPKEEP
11. BULLY
12. DEFAULT
13. PLAYER1
14. PLAYER2

**Attitude ID**

0. Abhor
1. Averse
2. Dispassionate
3. Dig
4. Adore

functions.name: PedIsFemale
functions.desc: Check whether the ped's gender is female or male.

functions.name: PedIsInVehicle
functions.desc: Returns true if the ped is riding a specific vehicle.

functions.name: PedIsValid
functions.desc: Check whether the ped is exist or not.

functions.name: PedSetHealth
functions.desc: Set the health of the existing pedestrian.

functions.name: PedSetMoney
functions.desc: Sets the new money amount for the ped.

functions.name: PlayerClearLastVehicle
functions.desc: Removes the last vehicle used by the player.

functions.name: PlayerSetHealth
functions.desc:
Sets the player's health.

Health can go as high as you want, but it is only meant to go to double the max health (that extra health being from the kissing bonus).

Unlike ```PedSetHealth```, this function will not change the player's max health if health is set higher.

By default, the player's max health is 200.

functions.name: PlayerSetPosSimple
functions.desc:
Set the player's position without extra behaviors. Will not behave correctly if the position is not loaded, so only use this for moving a short distance.

Unlike ```PlayerSetPosXYZ``` and ```PedSetPosXYZ```, this will not affect anything other than the player's position.

functions.name: RadarLockOnFloor
functions.desc:
Locks the radar to a specific layer of the minimap.

0 is outside, 1-3 are the floor layers.

functions.name: StopPedProduction
functions.desc: Stops generating any kind of Ambient peds.

functions.name: SystemIsReady
functions.desc:
Checks if the game is ready for most forms of scripting.

This is very important in any script that runs as soon as the game starts, and you should wait until it returns true before doing most things.

In a few cases, you may find it necessary to wait an additional second after the system is ready.

functions.name: TextPrintString
functions.desc:
Displays an arbitrary text on screen for the specified time in seconds.

Position must be 1 or 2.

params.name: text
params.desc: A string to be printed out.

functions.name: Wait
functions.desc: Pauses the script execution for specified amount of time in milliseconds.

functions.name: WeatherForceSnow
functions.desc: Forces upcoming weather to snow weather.

functions.name: WeatherGet
functions.desc: Returns the current weather ID.

functions.name: WeatherRelease
functions.desc: Allows the game to continue its usual weather pattern.

functions.name: WeatherSet
functions.desc: Sets game weather to specified ID.

variables.desc: Lua language version that Bully uses.

variables.desc: Representation of the global player object variable.

variables.name: FADE_IN_TIME
variables.desc: The time to takes the camera to fade in. (in millisecond)

variables.name: FADE_OUT_TIME
variables.desc: The time to takes the camera to fade out. (in millisecond)
